<Sect1 Id="ToFlipPartOfAnIconTA">
<Title>To Flip (Mirror) a Region of the Icon</Title>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>flipping icon</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>icons: flipping</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<OrderedList>
<ListItem Id="HICND.TSKS.item.157">
<Para>Select the Selection tool (bottom right of the palette).</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HICND.TSKS.item.158">
<Para>Press mouse button 1 and drag a box around the area you want to flip.</Para>
<Para>A box flashes around the selected area.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HICND.TSKS.item.159">
<Para>Choose Flip Area from the Edit menu and choose Vertical or Horizontal.</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
<Para>Flipping an area creates a pixel-for-pixel mirror image of the selected
area.</Para>
<Procedure>
